Got it 👍 let’s do a clean reset of PM2 properly (this will fix any weird state issues).

🔥 Step 1: Stop & delete all PM2 processes

pm2 stop all
pm2 delete all

🔥 Step 2: Kill PM2 daemon completely

pm2 kill

🔥 Step 3: Uninstall PM2 globally

npm uninstall -g pm2

🔥 Step 4: Reinstall fresh PM2

npm install -g pm2

🔥 Step 5: Start your app cleanly

cd /opt/files
pm2 start server.js --name my-app

🔍 Step 6: Verify it's running
pm2 status

👉 You should see:

my-app   online

🔥 Step 7: Test Node directly (VERY IMPORTANT)

curl http://localhost:4000/api/health

👉 Must return JSON like:

{"status":"ok"}
🔥 Step 8: Test NGINX
curl http://localhost

👉 Should now return your website ✅

🔥 Step 9: Make PM2 persistent (auto start after reboot)
pm2 save
pm2 startup

👉 It will give a command like:

sudo env PATH=$PATH:/usr/bin pm2 startup systemd -u root --hp /root

👉 Copy-paste and run that command

